---
import YoruLayout from '~/layouts/YoruLayout.astro';
import Schedule from '~/components/yoru/Schedule.astro';
import { SITE, DUES } from '~/data/site';
---

<YoruLayout>
  <section class="hero">
    <div class="hero-meta">
      <span><span class="dot"></span>Center for Aikido Study</span>
      <span>Cary, North Carolina</span>
      <span>Aikido Association of America</span>
    </div>
    <h1>To find harmony, look <em>inward</em>.</h1>
    <div class="hero-bottom">
      <p class="lede">A small nonprofit dojo training in the tradition of Fumio Toyoda Shihan. Volunteer instructors. Three nights a week plus Sunday open mat. No contracts.</p>
      <div class="hero-stat">Monthly dues<strong>${DUES.monthly}</strong></div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section>
    <div class="sec-header"><span class="sec-code">0.1</span><h2 class="section-title">Aikido is a <em>budo</em>, taught at your level of ability.</h2></div>
    <div class="two-col">
      <div class="col">
        <h3>The art</h3>
        <p class="prose">In Aikido we focus on movement, balance, posture, and your state of mind, and how this influences your connection with others. We look inwards to make changes in ourselves, so we can lead others to change.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="col">
        <h3>The dojo</h3>
        <p class="prose">A 501(c) nonprofit, operating under the guidance of Sensei Jon Whatley. All instructors volunteer their time. All dues maintain the dojo and the practice.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section>
    <div class="sec-header"><span class="sec-code">0.2</span><h2 class="section-title">Class <em>schedule</em>.</h2></div>
    <Schedule />
  </section>

  <div class="pull">To find harmony with another, you must first find it within yourself.<cite>合氣道 · The way of Aikido</cite></div>

  <section>
    <div class="sec-header"><span class="sec-code">0.3</span><h2 class="section-title">Stop by <em>anytime</em>.</h2></div>
    <p class="prose">If you are new to Aikido, join for one month and attend as many classes as you can. You will be paired with an instructor who will show you basic movements and how to safely train. After the introductory month, if you wish to continue, we set up your membership. Visitors are always welcome to observe a class.</p>
    <p style="margin-top: 48px;"><a href="/yoru/visit" class="cta">Plan your visit</a></p>
  </section>
</YoruLayout>
